result.execSummary:
The defendant Hanna M Farren-Sass was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 450.11(7)(h).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Hanna M Farren-Sass in court with attorney Barbara K Due.  David T. Malone appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  sdg

The defendant has complied with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.

On motion of the state, the court amended the charge to Possess/Illegally Obtained Prescription, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 450.11(7)(h), a class U Misdemeanor.   Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction to the amended charge.

Court sentenced defendant to serve THIRTY-TWO (32) DAYS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to any sentence with credit for THIRTY-TWO (32) DAYS served; TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.

Court orders defendant to pay all cost, fees and surcharges, including DNA surcharge by 01-19-2018 or a civil judgment to be entered WITH tax intercept.  Bail on deposit to be applied if applicable.
